HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 327
BY REPRESENTATIVE MCMAHEN
MILITARY AFFAIRS/NATL GD: Expresses support for continuing the Louisiana National
Guard Youth Challenge Program at Camp Minden and recognizes its importance to
Louisiana youth
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express support for maintaining and continuing the Louisiana National Guard Youth
3 Challenge Program at Camp Minden and to recognize the program's importance to
4 the youth and communities of North Louisiana and the state as a whole.
5 WHEREAS, the Louisiana National Guard Youth Challenge Program has provided
6 life-changing educational and leadership opportunities to at-risk youth throughout Louisiana
7 for many years; and
8 WHEREAS, the program located at Camp Minden serves young people from across
9 the state by helping participants develop discipline, responsibility, academic achievement,
10 leadership skills, and workforce readiness; and
11 WHEREAS, graduates of the program have gone on to obtain high school
12 equivalency diplomas, pursue higher education, enter military service, and become
13 productive members of their communities; and
14 WHEREAS, the Camp Minden location has developed experienced staff,
15 infrastructure, community partnerships, and regional support systems that contribute
16 significantly to the success of the program; and
17 WHEREAS, maintaining a Youth Challenge presence in North Louisiana helps
18 ensure geographic accessibility and opportunity for youth and families throughout the
19 northern region of the state; and
